   <titleInfo>
      <title>[Letter] 1790 May 12, Knoxville [Tennessee, to] James Ore / John Sevier</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter from Governor John Sevier to Colonel James Ore, dated May 12, 1790. Sevier is ordering Ore to go to the Cherokee Nation to find out their intentions towards a treaty. Sevier also asks Ore to recommend to the Cherokee the merits of an agrarian lifestyle over that of hunting. Sevier hopes that the Cherokee can be persuaded to part with more of their land. Sevier suggests they set up a trading post at Tellico. He also mentions the Law of Nations in relation to the Cherokees having more land than they can cultivate.</abstract>
